# Arquitectura web Ventas360

Angular standalone (sin NgModules). Backend: FastAPI REST. Target: PC + tablet.

## Carpetas

- `core/` — singleton: interceptors, guards, services, models, layout (shell + sidebar), state transversal
- `shared/` — presentacional (`ui/`, pipes, directives, validators); sin HTTP ni stores
- `features/<dominio>/` — `data-access/` + pantalla smart + `ui/` dumb + `<dominio>.routes.ts`
- `notifications/` — desacoplado (store Signals + transporte)
- Tokens en `src/styles/_tokens.scss` (nunca hardcodear breakpoints/colores)

## Reglas

1. Dumb (`shared/ui`, `features/*/ui`): solo `input()`/`output()`; OnPush; sin HTTP/stores.
2. Smart: una por pantalla; único que inyecta stores/services.
3. Un feature **nunca** importa otro feature; solo `core`, `shared` o su `data-access`.
4. data-access: `*.dto.ts` + `*.model.ts` + `*.mapper.ts` + `*.service.ts` + `*.store.ts`.
5. Estado: Signals en stores `providedIn: 'root'`; mutaciones solo en el store.
6. Auth: cookie httpOnly + `withCredentials` (no localStorage/sessionStorage para JWT).
7. Lazy loading: rutas en `features/<dominio>/<dominio>.routes.ts`.
8. Errores HTTP → interceptor → `NotificationStore`; no try/catch de toasts en pantallas.
9. Formularios: Reactive Forms tipados (`NonNullableFormBuilder`).
10. Storybook para `shared/ui`; Vitest (services/stores) + Playwright (flujos críticos).
